<center><font size=7><b>Dragontorc</b></font></center>
<center>Number of entries found: 6</center><p>
<center>
<table width=600>
<TR><TD bgcolor="blue" background=""><font color="white"><b><i>Tips</i></b></font></td></tr>
<TR><TD>	<B>Alan White</B> from Poole may
not be the first to finish
<I>Dragontorc</I> (see <A href="yr16_07.htm#Dragontorc">this month's
Frontlines</A>) but his knowledge
of the game is encyclopaedic -
he sent us a thirteen page hint
sheet! This month though
there's only room for one
cryptic message:<BR>
<I>Do not kill the hand,<BR>
Find something in the South,<BR>
That comes from the far East,<BR>
To use in the West.<BR></I>
	Err, cheers Alan. Ummm,
I'm sure they'll be letting you
out soon.
 <i>(Alan White in Your Spectrum issue 16)</i> 

<br><hr>
First off, follow the poem
closely. In the last sanctuary
there's a scroll that tells you
where to look for the crowns.
 <i>(Martin Edwards in Your Spectrum issue 17)</i> 

<br><hr>
If you find
yourself in the Druid's Last
Sanctuary and get transported
to a room without any doors
<I>(Careful Hex, we're trying to find one for you! Ed)</I> then
don't go spair, sorry despair -
just try your Leyrod!
 <i>(Evan Mason in Your Spectrum issue 21)</i> 

<br><hr>
On the first level search for a bow and trade this for a sickle with an elf. Cutting herbs with this will gain an ENERGISE spell.<br>

&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Also, under a slab there lies a jewel. Trade it likewise for a message which, taken to yet another slab, will reveal the second level: the Lost Vaults - do you not shudder? Those who wish to escape this level must find the letters EXIT - subtlety here! - and arrange them on top of the E to reveal yet another layer.
 <i>(Master Adventurer Walters Of Knotty Gree in Sinclair User issue 40)</i> 

<br><hr>
Hendrik von Braun of London, stepped up to offer help with Dragon Torc ... slightly foxed he was and incanted thus. "At henges use a Ley Rod all around and blue cubes to make the spirits bound. If snakes you fear then light a torch and be at peace." With that he vanished into the night, muttering to himself.
 <i>(Hendrik Von Braun in Sinclair User issue 42)</i> 
<br>
</td></tr>
<TR><TD bgcolor="blue" background=""><font color="white"><b><i>Multiface pokes</i></b></font></td></tr>
<TR><TD><table border="0">
<tr>
<td WIDTH="200" ALIGN="LEFT"><B><U>DESCRIPTION</B></U></TD>
<td WIDTH="200" ALIGN="LEFT"><B><U>POKE(s)</B></U></TD>
</TR>
<tr><td>Immunity</td><td>58337,255</td></tr>
</table><HR>I assume this POKE gives you immunity as I left the game running for two hours with
the character in a spot where I would constantly lose energy, and it was still running when
I went back to it...<br>

&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <i>(Gerard Sweeney in Hack Attack III)</i> 
<br>
</td></tr>
</table></center><P>
